<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1202,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,192,1202,1228]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Note</emphasis>
:—German botanist Horst Pfennig intended to publish this taxon as 
<taxonomicName authority="Pfennig in Heitz &amp; Zeller" box="[940,1082,1203,1229]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis box="[940,1082,1203,1229]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">S. tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this name remained a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">nomen nudum</emphasis>
according to ICN Article 38.1 (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[583,812,1238,1264]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" refId="ref6937" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[682,741,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The taxon was later published as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. E. Newton" authorityYear="2004" box="[1221,1316,1238,1265]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ballyi">
<emphasis box="[1221,1316,1238,1265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">S. ballyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Newton, L. E." pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="10 - 13" refId="ref6187" refString="Newton, L. E. (2004) Sansevieria ballyi, a name at last for a long-cultivated plant. British Cactus and Succulent Journal 22: 10 - 13. [https: // www. jstor. org / stable / 42793926]" type="journal article" year="2004">Newton (2004)</bibRefCitation>
without knowledge of Pfennig‘s intended name, to accomodate dwarf, stoloniferous rosette plants with very short leaves with a distinct rough surface and distinct colour banding and short inflorescences, from south-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[136,213,1347,1373]" name="Kenya" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Kenya</collectingCountry>
. Later, studies by 
<bibRefCitation author="Newton, L. E." box="[414,598,1346,1373]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="10 - 12" refId="ref6278" refString="Newton, L. E. (2010 b) Notes on Sansevieria ballyi, with description of a new cultivar. Sansevieria 22: 10 - 12." type="journal article" year="2010">Newton (2010b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mansfeld, P. A." box="[652,833,1346,1372]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="225 - 229" refId="ref6030" refString="Mansfeld, P. A. (2016) Sansevieria ballyi L. E. Newton (Asparagaceae) and newly found field notes. Bradleya 34: 225 - 229. https: // doi. org / 10.25223 / brad. n 34.2016. a 10" type="journal article" year="2016">Mansfeld (2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mansfeld, P. A." box="[844,902,1346,1372]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="24 - 35" refId="ref6078" refString="Mansfeld, P. A. (2017) Die beliebte Sansevieria ballyi und die wahre Geschichte ihrer Entdeckung. Sansevieria Online 5: 24 - 35." type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
) showed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. E. Newton" authorityYear="2004" box="[1008,1100,1346,1373]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ballyi">
<emphasis box="[1008,1100,1346,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">S. ballyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be common in south-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[136,209,1383,1409]" name="Kenya" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and to extend also into adjacent northeast 
<collectingCountry box="[701,805,1382,1408]" name="Tanzania" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. It exhibits a considerable variability in rosette size, leaf length, stolon length, and leaf colour ranging from pale green to almost white with transverse bands varying in width. A population with paler leaf colour and very smooth leaf surface at the northern edge of the species‘ distribution range was first published as a cultivar; 
<emphasis box="[511,642,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Sansevieria</emphasis>
‘Ann Robertson’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Newton, L. E." box="[853,1066,1490,1516]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="10 - 12" refId="ref6278" refString="Newton, L. E. (2010 b) Notes on Sansevieria ballyi, with description of a new cultivar. Sansevieria 22: 10 - 12." type="journal article" year="2010">Newton 2010b: 12</bibRefCitation>
) and its pale leaf colour was later concluded to be “normal variation within a species” (
<bibRefCitation author="Newton, L. E." box="[723,935,1526,1552]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="10 - 12" refId="ref6278" refString="Newton, L. E. (2010 b) Notes on Sansevieria ballyi, with description of a new cultivar. Sansevieria 22: 10 - 12." type="journal article" year="2010">Newton 2010b: 12</bibRefCitation>
). Later, the population was elevated to varietal rank as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Newton 2015: 11)" baseAuthorityName="Newton" baseAuthorityPageNumber="11" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[228,863,1562,1589]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ballyi" variety="robertsoniae">
<emphasis box="[228,432,1562,1589]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Sansevieria ballyi</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[492,634,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">robertsoniae</emphasis>
(Newton 2015: 11)
</taxonomicName>
. Plants with short, smooth leaves had already been collected back in 1960 by W. Rauh, Heidelberg [D = 
<collectingCountry box="[731,871,1598,1624]" name="Germany" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Deutschland</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[886,996,1598,1625]" name="Germany" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Germany</collectingCountry>
)] together with typical plants with rough surface at Mutomo Hills. The smooth-leaved plants were later seen as natural variation by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mansfeld, P. A." box="[1169,1448,1634,1660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" pagination="24 - 35" refId="ref6078" refString="Mansfeld, P. A. (2017) Die beliebte Sansevieria ballyi und die wahre Geschichte ihrer Entdeckung. Sansevieria Online 5: 24 - 35." type="journal article" year="2017">Mansfeld (2017: 33–34)</bibRefCitation>
. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Newton" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[304,597,1670,1697]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ballyi" variety="robertsoniae">
<emphasis box="[304,397,1670,1697]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">S. ballyi</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[455,597,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">robertsoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
falls within the range of variation encountered in 
